( ) () . (diag.panel )

my.panel.text <- function(x, ...) {
  mx <- as.character(round(mean(x),1))
  mystr <- paste(" \n", mx, sep="")
  h <- hist(x, plot = FALSE)
  xloc <- mean(h$breaks)
  yloc <- xloc
  text(xloc, yloc, mystr, cex=2, col=2)
}
par(family = "AppleGothic")
pairs(~height+weight+year, data=BMI, diag.panel=my.panel.text)

  • my.panel.text() x

* \(x\) \(-\pi\) \(\pi\) 100 \(sin(x)\) \(cos(x)\)
* \(y\) \(x\) 100 \(sin(x)\) \(cos(x)\) 

matplot.test <- function(){
  par(mfrow=c(1,2), family = "AppleGothic")
  x <- seq(-pi, pi, length = 100) # -pi ~ pi  100  
  y <- cbind(sin(x), cos(x)) # x sin  cos   
  matplot(x, y, type = "l", main = "") # x sin cos  
  matplot(y, type = "p", pch = 16, main = "  ") # y   x (1,100)
} # end function
matplot.test()

  • \(x\) \(x\) 1 100
